{"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"","text":"Pacino Docs  \u00b7 Open Source 8-issue OOO RISC-V Processor CORE AI co-designed I-CACHE D-CACHE MEM CTRL I/O I/O uarchlabs.github.io/pacino open source \u00b7 2026 // overview \"I'm out of order? You're out of order!\" <p>         Pacino is an open source 8-issue out-of-order RISC-V processor targeting the RVA23S64 profile. RTL is written in SystemVerilog, simulated with Verilator, and verified with a combination of directed tests, functional coverage, formal analysis via SymbiYosys and riscv-formal, and spike-dasm as an independent oracle. Gate synthesis targets Yosys with FPGA mapping via Quartus and Vivado. Design decisions, AI-assisted co-design records, and architectural rationale are committed alongside the RTL.       </p> // recent <p> \u25cf\u00a0 New: IA session browser, see  Sessions tab \u25cf\u00a0 BP-041 complete \u2014 TAGE CTR update testing \u00b7 2026.05.30 \u25cf\u00a0 BP-042-048 complete \u2014 TAGE/ITTAGE audits and design improvements; 2026.06.08 \u25cf\u00a0 TAGE/ITTAGE \u2014 unit testing complete; 2026.06.11 </p> // specs architectureRISC-V RVA23S64 issue width8-issue OOO rtl languageSystemVerilog simulatorVerilator 5.x compilerGCC 16.x, LLVM 22.x RISC-V statusactive // architecture frontendicache \u00b7 ftq \u00b7 ifu \u00b7 ibuf \u00b7 decode \u00b7 bpu dispatchrename \u00b7 prf (i/f/v/mm) \u00b7 rob \u00b7 reservation stations executeint \u00b7 float \u00b7 vector \u00b7 matrix \u00b7 atomics lsuagu \u00b7 lq \u00b7 sq \u00b7 fwd \u00b7 l1d \u00b7 vlsu \u00b7 mmlsu memoryl2 \u00b7 l3 \u00b7 prefetch mmuitlb \u00b7 dtlb \u00b7 l2tlb \u00b7 ptw uncoretilelink \u00b7 csr \u00b7 pmu \u00b7 trace protectionpma \u00b7 pmp // ai co-design methodology <p>Pacino is designed using a structured AI co-design methodology \u2014 a domain expert directing a dual-agent workflow across architectural planning and RTL implementation. Prompts, iteration history, and design rationale are committed alongside the RTL as first-class artifacts. Full methodology documentation is in the FAQ and the repo.</p> // get started view on github \u2197 read the docs \u2197 read the FAQ \u2190 uarchlabs pacino \u00b7 uarchlabs \u00b7 open source hardware \u00b7 \u00a9 2026 github.com/uarchlabs/pacino \u2197"},{"location":"overview/","title":"Pacino \u2014 microarchitecture overview","text":"<p>Pacino is an open source 8-issue out-of-order RISC-V processor targeting the RVA23S64 profile, designed using a structured AI co-design methodology. Click any block to explore the pipeline.</p> <p> </p>"},{"location":"overview/#documentation","title":"Documentation","text":"<p>The documentation follows the RTL cluster organization.</p> Unit Description Frontend instruction fetch, branch prediction, decode pipeline Backend rename, dispatch, out-of-order execution engine Memory subsystem load/store queues, scalar and vector memory access Cache subsystem L1D, L2 with TileLink/CHI interfaces MMU TLB hierarchy, page table walker, hypervisor support, PMP/PMA System CSR, exceptions, performance monitoring, debug"},{"location":"overview/#project-status","title":"Project status","text":"<p>Active development. RTL and documentation updated continuously. Open issues tracked in the GitHub repository.</p>"},{"location":"overview/#more-information","title":"More information","text":"Description Link Pacino overview This document. https://uarchlabs.github.io/pacino/overview/ Pacino landing page https://uarchlabs.github.io/pacino/ Pacino repo https://github.com/uarchlabs/pacino uarchlabs site https://uarchlabs.com/ uarchlabs blog Includes Pacino. https://uarchlabs.github.io/blog uarchlabs projects https://github.com/orgs/uarchlabs/repositories"},{"location":"sessions/","title":"Co-design sessions","text":""},{"location":"backend/overview/","title":"Overview",